<TITLE> BB cuts interest rates on import loans for essentials </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 14 (bdnews24.com)The central bank Tuesday asked retail banks to impose no more than 12 percent interest rates on import financing for essential commodities in the wake of the floods that battered major parts of the country. In a notice, Bangladesh Bank said the decision came to keep the imports flow normal to cope with the flood fallout. The new directiveeffective from Aug 14reduces the interest rates on import loans from as much as 16 percent. Bangladesh Bank said the floods had disrupted the country's internal farm output. "On the other hand, prices have gone up on the international market," it said. The twin problems kept the prices of essentials high on the local market, according to the central bank. The central bank directive, meant to ensure sufficient supply and put a leash on soaring prices of essential commodities, will cover rice, wheat, onion, pulses, sugar, edible oil, spices and dates. bdnews24.c
